keyword: how many calories in tater tots
title: How Many Calories in Tater Tots?
meta_description: Learn how many calories in tater tots per 85g serving, plus carbs, protein, fat, sodium, and tips for different cooking methods.
h1: How Many Calories in Tater Tots?
assumptions: Frozen commercial tater tots (e.g., Ore-Ida style), oven-baked per package directions, no added oil, salt, or toppings.
disclaimer: Nutrition varies by brand, size, cooking method, and added ingredients. Check packaging for exact values.

quick_answer.text: An 85g serving of oven-baked tater tots has about 145 kcal and 19.6g carbs.

label_note: Totals mirror Nutrition Facts labels for easy comparison.

tweaks.label: Add shredded cheese (1 oz per serving)

faqs.q: How many calories in one serving of tater tots?
faqs.a: About 145 kcal for an 85g oven-baked serving.

faqs.q: Are tater tots high in carbs?
faqs.a: Yes, around 23g carbs per 100g, mostly from potatoes.

faqs.q: What's the fat content in tater tots?
faqs.a: About 8.4g total fat per 100g, with 1.4g saturated.
Typically 0mg, as they're potato-based with vegetable oil.

faqs.q: How does cooking method affect calories in tater tots?
faqs.a: Oven-baked is lowest; deep-frying adds 40-60 kcal per serving from absorbed oil.
